originalText.text:
Had countless bad experiences which were all hard to imagine.
-We signed 1 year lease, right after one month we moved in, they decided to terminate the lease for selling it, without any apologies and explanations.

-Moved our furnitures without our agreement while we are out and used those for the staging pictures. (Picture is one of the examples how they moved away our belongings, and didn’t put back in the original places.)

-Someone in the building came in and stole our belongings and never tried to investigate.  It happened after we moved out but before we returned the keys. We still had one week of the lease left that time. They took a pair of brand new shoes, vacuum cleaners, coin jars away, those I planed to visit and organize again before the lease was up.
I asked wether anyone came in and took things away, and if so, it’s ok to just put things back. They just said no one would ever enter our unit. They didn’t tell us how the key are managed or try to check the security cameras.  They have serious security issues.
Some of our belongings were put back as nothing had happened after we asked for the explanations from senior manager, however we never got any explanations.

-After we moved out, they tried to charge us $500 for the damaging, which were existed before we moved in, good I took proof of pictures before we moved in..

-When we moved out, one of the neighbor came and asked what had happened, they also had some problems with the management company. Seems the company often manage to delete the bad reviews.
Once we wrote a bad review on FB group to warn our neighbors, the management company threatened us to not give our one month free rent which was agreed on the contract.

-It’s been 1.5 years since we moved out, but we still received the emails for the resident.(Maintenance schedules, no hot water issues, build events etc..)

You can imagine how poorly they manage the building.
